The chairmanship candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the Saturdayâ€™s FCT Area Council election, Mr. John Gabaya, has been declared winner of the election in Bwari Area Council. The Returning Officer for chairmanship election in Bwari, Professor Amuche Madu, declared Gabaya, who polled 13,045 votes to defeat his closest rival, Mr Haruna Shekwolo of All Progressives Congress (APC), who scored 7,697. Gabaya, was, therefore, returned elected having met the requirements of the Constitution and the electoral law.